  "orchestration_decision": "delegate",
  "decision_notes": "The problem is a constrained optimization task involving graph embedding/layout. It requires translating topological relations into a spatial grid layout while maximizing empty space.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "graph_modeling",
      "instructions": "Parse the input city map to represent it as a graph where nodes are colored regions and edges represent color-adjacency. Identify connectivity constraints and the set of unique colors/regions that must be placed on the grid."
    },
    {
      "label": "spatial_optimization",
      "instructions": "Given the graph of regions, find an embedding onto a 50x50 grid such that all adjacent regions in the graph are adjacent on the grid (horizontally or vertically). Use a packing algorithm or constraint satisfaction approach to minimize the total area occupied by the regions, thereby maximizing the number of empty cells (E)."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "Combine the graph model with the optimized grid layout. Verify that all adjacency and connectivity constraints are met in the resulting 50x50 grid, then calculate the number of empty cells E and format the output as FINAL_ANSWER: <grid> and JUSTIFICATION: <explanation of the layout strategy and E value>."
}
```

